This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning models, specifically topic models. The paper discusses methods to improve the interpretability of topic models, which is a common problem in the field of computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses document retrieval tasks, which suggests a connection to information retrieval (cs.IR). The evaluation of the re-ranking methods involves crowdworkers, which suggests a connection to human computation (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the importance of word frequency and relative importance, which suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL).
